Springbok captain, Siya Kolisi, raises the Webb Ellis cup at The Union Buildings in Pretoria during the Rugby World Cup Trophy Tour on November 7, 2019. PRETORIA - South Africans are lining the streets of Gauteng, to get a glimpse of their heroes, and that of the Webb Ellis Cup also known as Bill. The Rugby World Cup Trophy Tour kicked off on Thursday morning in Pretoria and is making its way through Johannesburg to Soweto. READ: IN PICTURES: World champions Springboks return home In the next few days, the team will make its way to Durban, East London, Port Elizabeth and Cape Town.  Pretoria prepares to welcome the Springboks after their victory at the Rugby World Cup on November 7, 2019. Cyril Ramaphosa addresses the Springboks in Pretoria on November 7, 2019. Springboks fans begin their celebrations early at the Union building in Pretoria during the Springbok Trophy Tour on November 7, 2019. Springboks fans wait for their turn to catch a glimpse of the Webb Ellis Cup and the triumphant Springbok team on November 7, 2019. The Springboks at the Union Buildings in Pretoria on November 7, 2019. Proud president, Cyril Ramaphosa poses with Springbok Captain, Siya Kolisi and coach Rassie Erasmus on November 7, 2019. The Springboks on the bus during their Rugby World Cup Tour on November 7, 2019. The Springboks travel around Pretoria in their customized tour bus on November 7, 2019. The Springboks celebrate their win on November 7, 2019. The Springboks pose with their fans on November 7, 2019. The Webb Ellis Cup travels around South Africa with the Springboks on November 7, 2019.